    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "K&amp;R C defines the <code>%</code> operator as producing the <b>remainder</b>, but names it the <b>modulus</b> operator. Confusingly, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modulo_operation\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modulo_operation</a> says that the <i>modulo</i> operation produces the <b>remainder</b>, both in computing and in mathematics... but also claims &quot;The range of numbers for an integer modulo of n is 0 to n − 1.&quot;!"
