      "creation_date" : 1538155568,
      "post_id" : 41534116,
      "comment_id" : 92058833,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "This is almost certainly slower because it  has a branch, unless you know that the input will mostly be positive.  If its random, then the branch prediction penalty will cost more clock cycles than an extra remainder calculation on most CPUs.  Or, if you want to conditionally add a value based on whether an int is negative or not, try <code>(maybeNegative &gt;&gt; 31) ^ thingToMaybeAdd + thingToAddTo</code>"
    } ],
